  "texts": [
    "Since LLMs often struggle in reasoning with numbers and mathematics, in Window2Text we preferred to avoid absolute timestamps, considering instead relative temporal relationships between states by adopting temporal adverbs (e.g., \"Then\", \"After 3 seconds\") and reporting the duration of the states (e.g., \"for 5 seconds\").",
    "Since we provide an anchor to absolute time by reporting the approximate time of the day at the beginning of the window description, the reported events are also approximately anchored in time.",
    "The above strategy is based on the observation that LLMs tend to perform better with qualitative information, as they can focus on understanding the sequence and relationships of sensor states rather than managing exact time calculations.",
    "In Section 4.4.3, we compare our approach with an alternative prompt using exact timestamps.",
    "Example 3.1."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}